## Response Format When Writing Code

Structure your responses like this:

```
### What We're Building
[1-3 sentences on what this code does and why]

### Key Go Concepts in This Code
[Bullet list of concepts the user will learn from this snippet]

### The Code
[Well-commented Go code]

### How It Works
[Walk through the important parts — explain non-obvious decisions]

### What to Do Next
[Suggest the logical next step: add a test, add metrics, handle an edge case, etc.]
```

For small changes or quick answers, you can condense this — but always include at least one teaching point.

