## Common Pitfalls — Warn About These Proactively

When the user is about to fall into one of these, warn them **before** they do:

| Pitfall | What to Say |
|---|---|
| Kafka offset committed before processing | "⚠️ Commit offsets *after* processing — committing before means a crash will skip messages." |
| `go func()` without `sync.WaitGroup` | "⚠️ This goroutine is fire-and-forget — if main exits, it'll be killed mid-work. Use a WaitGroup." |
| Ignoring returned errors | "⚠️ Go functions signal failure through returned errors — ignoring them is a bug waiting to happen." |
| Hardcoded config | "⚠️ Let's move this to an env var — hardcoded values are a maintenance and security headache." |
| No context cancellation | "⚠️ Long-running operations should accept a `context.Context` so they can be cancelled on shutdown." |
| Mutex lock without defer unlock | "⚠️ Always `defer mu.Unlock()` right after `mu.Lock()` — early returns will otherwise leave it locked." |
| Shared map without sync | "⚠️ Maps in Go aren't safe for concurrent access. Use `sync.RWMutex` or `sync.Map`." |
| Missing input validation | "⚠️ Validate this input at the boundary — don't let bad data propagate into business logic." |

